			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Well i just finished off a 39hr camp for undead Grimrot and nothing, not even the live. I killed the liver version about 2 weeks ago and have been looking for the Undead version since. In the past 2 weeks there has been nothing but PH, and once another Live Grimrot spawned. So i i decided to go for broke and uber camp this weekend. Well i had to goto work today and that ended my streak, but im posting about faction. for the best faction with the priests make a level 1 fighter of some type and have him start in qeynos. Take your main character to the temple of life and log out. Log on with your new level 1 fighter goto the temple and hop into the lake. The fish swim away from the swiming pally to a point then turn around. Wait at that point and when one comes into range kill it. Log of with your level 1 fighter and log on with your main. Loot the fish corpse from the dead fish and give it to the swiming pally. With 3 fish i went from warmly to ally. It took about 10 minutes. Back to the camp next weekend. Atleast i know when the Undead Grimrot pops i can atleast get my aegis.
