	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Here is the definitive manner in which to camp Lord Grimrot.  I'm in the middle of camping this item right now.  I've done all the reading and planned my strategy.  What I've come up with?  Forget it all.  Sit there and watch, wait and re-write what others have tried to quantify.  Here's what I've got so far.<BR>
<BR>
**********************<BR>
At first I thought that he would just pop on me and I would get lucky.  Wrong.  He really is, that rare.  As such, park yourself at the undead camp and watch.  It's mind-numbingly boring, but do it anyway.<BR>
<BR>
Lord Grimrot spawns in two versions; low level skel verstion and higher level (35max) human form.  Either can drop the heart/scythe (ensure the scythe you use is the nodrop one).<BR>
<BR>
His PH is a Putrid Skeleton.  It spawns under the central little tower with *nothing on it*.  There are several with no lanterns on them, but this is generally in the center of the camp.  The PH can be confused with another Putrid Skeleton that spawns and collapses right again one of the legs of this stand.  Do not be fooled.  The REAL PH --does not fall--.  He always wields a rusty Broadsword, and instead of threatening you with some obscure Norrathian villain, he simply says, &quot;Die like the fool you are.&quot; when attacked.  That is your PH.<BR>
<BR>
Now, my first attempts have been at killing everything.  Just wax everything, you'll earn bone chips for faction with Lashun Novashine in Qeynos, and the Putrids get you Priests of Life faction on every kill.  Some guides to the Grimrot spawn suggest doing faction work until &quot;you no longer see the faction change&quot;.  This is no longer realistic as they have all but removed the cieling on faction with the addition of ALLY FACTION.  Just keep conning the Quest NPC until you get ALLY and then do some more faction.  Frankly I'd rather blow 5pp/stack of bone chips and toss a few gp to Lashun after ALLY to ensure I don't have to do the camp again!<BR>
<BR>
Now.  Since my first attempts to make him spawn were done by clearing the camp (including PH) I tried to time the PH spawn.  From what I can tell at this point (these are concrete, btw) the PH is on a 3hr12m --&gt; 3hr25m timer.  He can spawn anywhere inside those times, and perhaps on the outside few minutes before and after the last PH KILL.  I clear the camp for peace of mind at this point, and if unsuccessful in the next day or so, will try allowing the camp to stay popped and simply watch for the PH.  Since no other mobs pop in EXACTLY the same spot, it's feasible the PH will still pop on the same schedule with a full pop up.<BR>
<BR>
Hope this helps... more to come.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
