				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Well i just finished reading ALL 9 pages of this thread and i doubt anyone else will but here goes...<BR>
<BR>
My experience when something like this:<BR>
I'm walking along the river edge on my way to kith to retrieve my corpse(11 paladin, chief Gan`Shralok got me on my way to freeport:() and i was taking a break in the tower trying to get a sow and noticed a gaurd at the toip by the fire, never having seen anything there before i went to investigate, i got to the top and found a gaurd named capt something(can't remember his exact name but it was capt not captian) and so i hialed him and the conversation went something like this:<BR>
you say 'Hail capt something'<BR>
Capt something says 'Hail traveler! watch your step during your travels, my gaurds have reported many [local hazards] and some [rumors of corruption].'<BR>
you say 'what local hazards?'<BR>
Capt something says 'My gaurds have reported sightings of lord grimrot in the southern plains of karana.'<BR>
(please note that not all of it may be correct i was in a bit of a hurry to get my corpse as i felt rather nakedf without my armor:))<BR>
<BR>
after that fun little conversation i decided to go to sk and see if i could find this &quot;lord grimrot&quot; i thought it might be fun to just take a look at him, by his name i figured he was a named griff(grimfeather - grimrot) so i zone into SK and i hear someone yell &quot;train!&quot; and i thought &amp;$^$, so i ducked off the bridge to my left almost in the water and started looking both ways and finally saw what looked like a HT partical effect and someone running toward me, so i backed up a bit so as not to be aggroed(beings everything that passed by was red to me) and i saw that the MOB was a human named lord grimrot! i had no idea what he was for so i just waited for him to move and zoned back to get my corpse, now that i know what he's for i zone in once in awhile to see if anyone shouts something about him but nothing yet, probably missed my chance to get the AoL:\ oh well, someday i'll get him...<BR>
thats my story, i'll post again if i see anything new...<BR>
<BR>
Laben, 11th HEF paladin<BR>
Vazealle<BR>
<BR>
P.S. when asked about the rumors of corruption Capt gave me a quest to kill corrupt gaurds and said something along these lines: 'Some of my gaurds have reported suspisions of corruption to me, if you find you must kill one return his gaurd bracer to me, i can't have this. but make sure he is corrupt or i will have your head too.' this may not be exactly right but i plan to try this quest with my 40 druid on brell using track for Capt to see what the prize is(most likely good faction and some coin), well thats all for now, good luck!:)
